.TH "dspio_scp" 9 "dspio_scp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dspio_scp \- Prepare and send the SCP message to DSP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dspio_scp
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "int mod_id "  ","
.BI "int src_id "  ","
.BI "int req "  ","
.BI "int dir "  ","
.BI "const void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "void *reply "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *reply_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "mod_id" 12
ID of the DSP module to send the command
.IP "src_id" 12
ID of the source
.IP "req" 12
ID of request to send to the DSP module
.IP "dir" 12
SET or GET
.IP "data" 12
pointer to the data to send with the request, request specific
.IP "len" 12
length of the data, in bytes
.IP "reply" 12
point to the buffer to hold data returned for a reply
.IP "reply_len" 12
length of the reply buffer returned from GET
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns zero or a negative error code.
